-## How Connectivity Helps Sophisticated Subsystems Converge Efficiently
-
-This package should help convergence in six concrete ways.
-
-### 1. Shared signal vocabulary
-
-Subsystems should not invent incompatible local meanings for "important", "blocked", or "done".
-
-Connectivity gives them a common typed vocabulary, which reduces translation overhead and brittle ad hoc glue.
-
-### 2. Early conflict surfacing
-
-Specialists often disagree before the coordinator notices.
-
-Connectivity should make conflict and uncertainty signals cheap to emit and cheap to recognize so synthesis can adapt before a full fan-in stall occurs.
-
-### 3. Efficient fan-in
-
-Instead of waiting for every subsystem to submit a narrative report, the coordinator should be able to react to:
-
-- blocker
-- high-confidence convergence
-- urgent policy issue
-- synthesis-ready partial result
-
-That reduces latency and token waste.
-
-### 4. Reduced redundant work
